public final class OsmPbfGraphLoader extends PbfGraphLoader
Loads OSM data from PBF format into a GraphStore. During this process, ways are broken up into edges in a process referred to as "way sectioning". Way sectioning is performed by a WaySectioningGraphLoader, which takes OSM ways (in the form of a raw graph where each edge is a complete way) and breaks them down. This process is fairly complex and significantly slows the process of loading OSM graphs versus UniDb graphs, which are already sectioned into edges during processing by the data team.
Author:
jonathanl (shibo)
